    <h1>User Guide v1.0</h1>
    <p>The Online Power Flow Assessment Tool was designed as a fast, lightweight mobile-ready tool that can perform detailed computation of power flow for an unlimited number of busses in a given 3-phase network.
    </p>
    <p>The tool supports excel file upload for bus and line data. Examples can be downloaded by clicking <a href="/download/bus">HERE</a> for bus data, and <a href="/download/line">HERE</a> for line data.</p>
    <h1>How to Run</h1>
    <ol>
      <li>Populate your data into a csv file following the format provided in the example csvs (Can be downloaded above)</li>
      <li>Navigate to the <a href="/">homepage</a> and upload your respective bus and line data csvs and hit submit.</li>
      <li>The tool will scan your data, build a schematic representation and allow you to perform a final check to ensure correctness before submitting</li> 
      <li>Then click RUN!</li>
      <li>The results will be displayed to you and can be convieniently downloaded in csv format</li>
    </ol>
    <h1>How it works</h1>
    <p>The tool works by analyzing your input data and first calculating the voltage, angle, real and reactive power values using the iterative Newton Rahpson method. The calculated parameters are then used to calculate the line flows and losses for the system.</p>
